## Request Parameters
<a name="API_wafRegional_GetRegexPatternSet_RequestParameters"></a>

For information about the parameters that are common to all actions, see [Common Parameters](CommonParameters.md).

The request accepts the following data in JSON format.

 ** [RegexPatternSetId](#API_wafRegional_GetRegexPatternSet_RequestSyntax) **   <a name="WAF-wafRegional_GetRegexPatternSet-request-RegexPatternSetId"></a>
The `RegexPatternSetId` of the [RegexPatternSet](API_wafRegional_RegexPatternSet.md) that you want to get. `RegexPatternSetId` is returned by [CreateRegexPatternSet](API_wafRegional_CreateRegexPatternSet.md) and by [ListRegexPatternSets](API_wafRegional_ListRegexPatternSets.md).  
Type: String  
Length Constraints: Minimum length of 1. Maximum length of 128.  
Pattern: `.*\S.*`   
Required: Yes

## Response Syntax
<a name="API_wafRegional_GetRegexPatternSet_ResponseSyntax"></a>

{
   "RegexPatternSet": { 
      "Name": "string",
      "RegexPatternSetId": "string",
      "RegexPatternStrings": [ "string" ]
   }
}

## Response Elements
<a name="API_wafRegional_GetRegexPatternSet_ResponseElements"></a>

If the action is successful, the service sends back an HTTP 200 response.

The following data is returned in JSON format by the service.

 ** [RegexPatternSet](#API_wafRegional_GetRegexPatternSet_ResponseSyntax) **   <a name="WAF-wafRegional_GetRegexPatternSet-response-RegexPatternSet"></a>
Information about the [RegexPatternSet](API_wafRegional_RegexPatternSet.md) that you specified in the `GetRegexPatternSet` request, including the identifier of the pattern set and the regular expression patterns you want AWS WAF to search for.   
Type: [RegexPatternSet](API_wafRegional_RegexPatternSet.md) object

